OL,3,CReporting on Storm Desmond while the
OL,4,Cfloods hit home
OL,6,FWith the A7 impassable all I could do
OL,7,Fwas follow developments on the radio
OL,8,Fand online as I ate a glum dinner with
OL,9,Fthe barman in an otherwise empty
OL,10,Fdining room, wondering what I would
OL,11,Freturn to find.
OL,13,FAs it turned out I was very fortunate.
OL,14,FAlthough the water outside my home was
OL,15,Fankle deep as I walked to my front
OL,16,Fdoor, the house itself was flood free.
OL,17,FI escaped the fate of so many
OL,18,Fhomeowners by inches as the water
OL,19,Flevel peaked just shy of the front
OL,20,Fstep.
