OL,3,CReporting on Storm Desmond while the
OL,4,Cfloods hit home
OL,6,FMore than 2,000 properties weren't as
OL,7,Flucky, including people just a dozen
OL,8,Fhouses down the road.
OL,10,FThe floods, for the second time in ten
OL,11,Fyears, proved just how powerless we
OL,12,Fare when nature flexes its
OL,13,Fconsiderable muscle.
OL,15,FBy the time I returned to Carlisle the
OL,16,Fflooding had just hit its height. My
OL,17,Fneighbours and I stood on our
OL,18,Fdoorsteps taking in the scene and
OL,19,Fhoping that no more rain would fall.
