OL,3,CReporting on Storm Desmond while the
OL,4,Cfloods hit home
OL,6,FLike I said, I was exceptionally
OL,7,Flucky. Friends of mine who had lost
OL,8,Feverything in the floods of 2005, in
OL,9,Fwhat was supposed to be a once in a
OL,10,Fcentury flooding event were going
OL,11,Fthrough the same painful, stressful
OL,12,Fprocess all over again just ten years
OL,13,Flater.
OL,15,FFor some it was the final straw. Many
OL,16,Fleft the area in the months that
OL,17,Ffollowed unwilling or unable to trust
OL,18,Fthat this would be the final time
OL,19,Ftheir homes would be ruined unless
OL,20,Fthey moved their lives to properties
OL,21,Fon higher ground.
